more information



Our phones are basically OpenVPN clients with VOIP phones behind them. Physically, they are a router, a small hardware client plugged into that, and a landline plugged into the client. We prefer to get wired internet to the router via a CAT5 cable, although wireless connectivity is possible, and the router and hardware client need to be plugged into wall power. Bandwidth maxes at 115 KBPS and power at 12 watts when in use, less when idle. This flyer gives an overview:

https://github.com/kra/futel/blob/master/media/public_telephones.pdf